er than that of a nonrotating WD of average mass ($0.6\\, M_\\odot$), which\nis on the order of $7\\times 10^3$~km. The effects on the minimum mass of\nJ2056-3014 due to changes in the temperature and composition of the stellar\nmatter were found to be negligibly small.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Oct 2020 14:32:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Oct 2021 13:24:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-08"}
